						<div class="postbody">The <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC5_audio" class="postlink">MMC5 audio page</a> on the wiki states that &quot;the polarity of all MMC5 channels is reversed compared to the APU.&quot;<br /><br />What does that mean, exactly?  Should the 0s and 1s in the APU's duty cycle sequences be swapped?<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Duty&nbsp; &nbsp; Waveform sequence<br />0&nbsp; &nbsp;0 1 0 0 0 0 0 0 (12.5%)<br />1&nbsp; &nbsp;0 1 1 0 0 0 0 0 (25%)<br />2&nbsp; &nbsp;0 1 1 1 1 0 0 0 (50%)<br />3&nbsp; &nbsp;1 0 0 1 1 1 1 1 (25% negated)<br /></div></div>

					
