			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It means that if the NES squares produce a positive voltage on a &quot;1&quot;, the MMC5 squares doing the equivalent thing will produce a negative voltage.<br /><br />I would suggest inverting the output. Don't make changes to the internal digital logic before output. Simply exchanging 1 and 0 is not the right idea, as remember this squares also have a volume control. 0 should still output 0, and this makes a difference especially if you are simulating an analog filter on the output. If you could replace 1 with -1, that would be conceptually more like what you want, but it would only be the correct implementation if you are multiplying it with the volume and not using some boolean logic on the volume.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
