						<div class="postbody">Yes, that is correct.<br /><br />It's standard for a lot of audio devices to include a mild highpass filter to get rid of DC offset, because it can reduce amplifier headroom, cause inefficient use of power, or cause other problems for an audio system. You also can't hear a DC offset.</div>

